{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OrangeThemeSelectInputComponentTokensProvider","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Define your own provider for select input component tokens","    \/\/ by inheriting from existing provider","    class CustomSelectInputComponentTokensProvider: OrangeThemeSelectInputComponentTokensProvider {","","        \/\/ Then override the select input component tokens you want.","","        override var selectSizeMaxHeightContainerIcon: SizeSemanticToken { DimensionRawTokens._600 }","","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ Or define your own provider from scratch","    class CustomSelectInoutComponentTokensProvider: SelectInputComponentTokens {","","        \/\/ And implement hunders of tokens.","        \/\/ You are allowed to give semantic tokens providers if you want to define values.","    }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, you can give this "},{"code":"CustomSelectInputComponentTokensProvider","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to your own theme implementation:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["class LocalTheme: OrangeTheme {","","    override init() {","        super.init(selectInput: CustomSelectInputComponentTokensProvider())","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"or to an already existing theme for example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    OrangeTheme(selectInput: CustomSelectInputComponentTokensProvider())"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also possible to use your own semantic tokens providers for this component tokens providers:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Uses by default here:","    \/\/ 